			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would like to replace some existing summons spells with summonable augments that have equivalent effects.  For example, replace the focus effect equipment items with augments.
<br />

<br />
The benefit to me would be that these spells would not lose their utility as equipment quality ramps.  Very few people want to swap out their normal gear for a summonable focus item, but I suspect there are people who would like to benefit from the focus effects if they didn't have to remove their normal gear.
<br />

<br />
I think that the benefit wouldn't only be realized with the focus effect items, but also things like coldstone vision, saving throw protection (e.g. elemental blanket), etc.
<br />

<br />
I fear that this might be difficult to implement due to coding issues.  Code might have to change to allow integration of augments in places other than the "birdbaths."  "No Rent" augmentations might cause difficulties since it would be important that only the augment, and not the augmented item, "poof" when a character is offline for a sufficiently long period of time.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row2" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
